Installing Dockers on Ubuntu

1.Start the ubuntu server and log in.
2.Run sudo apt-get remove docker docker-engine docker.io. That is to remove the old version of docker if there is any.
3.Run sudo apt-get update, to update the server.
4.Run Sudo snap install docker, to install docker on your server. 
5.Run sudo docker run hello-world, to pull an image from the docker hub to make sure the installation is working.
6.Run sudo systemctl status docker to check if it is active.
 

Installing Kubernetes on ubuntu

1.After logging in to the ubuntu server run the following command Curl -s https://packages.cloud.google.com/apt/doc/apt-key.gpg | sudo apt-key add
2.Then run sudo apt-get install curl
3.Run sudo apt-add-repository “deb http://apt.kubernetes.io/ Kubernetes-xenial main”. To add  Kubernetes Repositories.
4.Run sudo apt-get install kubeadm kubelet kubectl. To install Kubernetes tools.
5.Run sudo apt-mark hold kubeadm kubelet kubectl.
6.Confirm installation by running kubeadm version
 

Install Ansible on ubuntu server

1.Run sudo apt-add-repository ppa:ansible/ansible. To add ansible repository.
2.Run sudo apt-get update. To update the server.
3.Run sudo apt-get install ansible. To install the ansible tools.
4.Run ansible –version. To check installation
 

Install Minikube on ubuntu

1.Run Curl -lo https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikune-linux-amd64
2.Run chmod +x minkube-linux-amd64. To make minikube executable. 
3.Run minikube version. To verify minikube installation. 
 
